[24:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'That\'s just part of the process. So, what I\'m going to do now is play the video and start making those adjustments. And I\'m going to speed this part up a bit because it\'s pretty simple. The main thing is just making sure the voice-over matches the visuals so'

[24:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'everything stays in sync. Once that\'s done, the whole thing starts to feel like a proper video instead of separate clips. So, yeah, I\'ll just speed through this section. All right, so here\'s a quick recap of exactly what I did. It\'s the 4th of March, 2023.'

[24:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'A marble hall in downtown Dubai. A man walks onto the stage. He clicks a remote. The lights dim.'

[25:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Behind him, something appears on the screen. A ring of glass rooms. But they\'re not in the sky. They\'re not on land. They\'re under the sea.'

[25:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So why is one of the richest cities on Earth building down instead of up? Here\'s the thing. Dubai is running out of room. The towers can\'t climb any higher.'

[25:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The fake islands are almost full. So where do you go when there\'s nowhere left to go? You go under. For the voiceover, I split everything'

[25:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'into multiple chunks and intentionally left small gaps between them. Now, the reason I did that is because I wanted to build suspense. If you look at channels like Fern, you\'ll notice they often use these natural pauses that create'

[25:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'anticipation and keep viewers locked in. That\'s exactly the effect I was going for here. So most of those gaps you see in the timeline are actually intentional. They\'re there for pacing, not mistakes. Now, the fast cuts you see'

[26:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'in the video were actually generated by the model itself. So I didn\'t really need to manually edit those. They were already built into the prompt structure. I also went through and adjusted the audio levels. Some clips were a bit too loud or didn\'t sit well with the'

[26:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'narration. So I just reduced their volume where needed. After that, I stretched the background music to make sure it covered the full duration of the video smoothly from start to finish. And that\'s basically it. Now, Fern does also use a mix of realistic footage and'

[26:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
