[27:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'use that to generate the first batch of thumbnails. Now, as you probably know, most image models actually perform way better when you give them a reference image. So, if you go back to the source PDF in the master prompt and scroll'

[28:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'through it, you\'ll see I added a couple of thumbnail references in there. What you can do is just take screenshots of those references, and then attach them inside Google Flow whenever you\'re generating each thumbnail variation. And'

[28:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the reason we do this is to keep everything consistent. So, all your thumbnails have the same style and don\'t feel random or disconnected. [music] For example, this is what we got when we used the prompt without any reference.'

[28:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Now, I\'m going to take that exact same prompt again, but this time, I\'ll attach a reference image from the source material file and send it along with the prompt. [music] And you\'ll notice something interesting.'

[28:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The output completely changes, even though the prompt is exactly the same. That\'s basically why references are so powerful because they guide the model into the exact visual direction you want.'

[28:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Now we\'ve got the second output after attaching a reference. And as you can see, this one looks noticeably better. At first glance, you might think both results look the same, but if you look closely at the details, you\'ll notice the version with the reference image'

[29:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'looks more polished and more professional overall. Now what I\'m going to do next is take every single thumbnail prompt variant that Claude gave me and run them one by one. And for each one, I\'m going to attach the same reference image inside'

[29:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Google Flow so we can keep the style consistent and also compare which thumbnail stands out the most. So, I\'ll just keep copying each prompt and pasting it into Flow one after the other. Now, since we\'ve got unlimited'

[29:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
