[32:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'device. So, what that means is someone watching on mobile will see a different portion compared to someone on TV or desktop. Because of that, you need a proper guide to know where to place your key elements, so nothing important gets'

[32:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'cut off. Now, I already have a template for that, so I\'m going to upload it into Canva and place it into my workspace. Then, I\'ll set it as a background image so I can clearly see the safe zones and structure everything properly inside'

[32:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'them. Now, the key thing you need to understand is that you should always place your most important elements inside that red underlined area. That area is basically the universally visible zone, meaning it\'s what shows properly across all devices in YouTube,'

[33:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'whether someone is on mobile, desktop, or TV. So, for anything important, that\'s where it has to go. Now, for me, I\'m just going to add a simple text element that says "New videos weekly." After that, I\'ll change the font to'

